    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Your two favors came safe. Pray forward the inclosed after reading it. I have not
                        <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0254">the Edda</title></bibl>:
                        <persName ref="pe0026">White</persName> had it but was too dear &amp; indeed
                    of no great use to me. I wish <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> see <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0253">Bartholinus de Contempt..
                            mortis</title></bibl> &amp; <unclear reason="illegible">Dasius</unclear>. This week I hope to finish my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0012">welsh Tour</title></bibl> &amp; be quite at liberty for my
                    friends service.<note type="editorial">The first edition of Pennant's <hi rend="italic">Tour in Wales</hi> was published in 1778.</note></p>
                <closer><salute>I am <lb/>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> affect. humble Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Jan. 23<hi rend="superscript">d.</hi>1778.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
